    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS) - MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER - MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER INSTALL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="x0301205" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER INSTALL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <specpara>
                <para>Prior to installing the MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER assembly, a careful inspection of component parts
                    including tapered leaf spring mounting bushing should be undertaken. Only authorized International
                    parts should be used in the installation procedure.
                </para>
            </specpara>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Main Support Member Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate main support member end with
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301214">(Figure 13, Item 5)</hotlnk>
                    bushing assembly, at the forward suspension mounting bracket
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_18.xml" xrefid="f0301223">(Figure 22, Item 1)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert bolt and hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place axle seat bracket on main support member with alignment pin, axle seat bracket
                    forward mark indicator should be facing in forward direction.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place u-bolts and u-bolt axle top mounting bracket on axle assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install air spring assembly to top bracket mounted on chassis frame
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_16.xml" xrefid="f0301217">(Figure 16, Item 4).</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align and install lower u-bolt mounting plate, install u-bolt nuts and hand tighten
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_17.xml" xrefid="f0301219">(Figure 18, Items 2 and 3)</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert mounting nut on air spring threaded stud, hand tighten.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and install shock absorber to upper shock absorber mounting bracket, install
                    bolts and hand tighten
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_17.xml" xrefid="f0301221">(Figure 20, Items 1, 2 and 3).</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate and install shock absorber lower bolts at bracket mounted on tapered leaf spring
                    assembly, and hand tighten
                    <hotlnk document="s03012_17.xml" xrefid="f0301222">(Figure 21).</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place lower air spring mounting stud in applicable mounting hole in rear of tapered leaf
                    spring
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0301214">(Figure 13, Item 1).</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten all mounting hardware to appropriate values as indicated on the torque chart.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">When all torque requirements are met and installations complete, follow procedures for
                    re-inflating suspension to proper ride height. See the first section and appropriate subsection for
                    correct ride height procedures.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0301214" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg03/G0301214.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Main Support Member</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. AIR SPRING LOWER MOUNTING LOCATION</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER SHOCK ABSORBER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MAIN SUPPORT MEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. AUXILIARY LEAF</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. AXLE SEAT LOCATOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
